# Core API flow documentation (mandatory)

When you change **non–simple-CRUD** API behavior — anything with multi-step domain logic, thresholds, LLM calls, or hybrid search — you **must** update **`docs/CORE_API_FLOWS.md`** in the **same** change set so it stays accurate (handlers → services → storage, algorithms, thresholds).

**Treat as core (doc must stay in sync):** e.g. `POST /api/v1/documents` ingest (hot/cold), `POST /api/v1/query/progressive`, `POST /api/v1/tags/group`, `GET /api/v1/hot/*`, `GET /api/v1/cold/doc_source`, `GET /api/v1/tags` when filtering/group semantics change, and MCP tools that mirror those flows (`internal/api/handler_execute.go`, `internal/service/svcimpl/*`, `internal/storage/memory/index.go`, related jobs).

**Simple pass-through (no CORE_API_FLOWS refresh required unless the doc explicitly lists them):** plain list/get by id, summaries/chapters by document id, tag groups list, quota, metrics, health — unless their **contract or side effects** become non-trivial.

If you add a **new** core endpoint or materially new stage in an existing flow, add or extend the matching section in `docs/CORE_API_FLOWS.md` (English).
